	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Nov 27th 12:33 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay, peeps...let me end this argument with some of what I like to call "logic".<br>This shield is a POS by any standards.<br>Ok...lets assume that we are dealing with a lowbie who is actually grouping to loot this and actually breaks a sweat to do so.<br>-&nbsp;&nbsp;Hella heavy.  'nuf said<br>-  Anyone who is high enough to even group against the prince to get this shield can't scrounge up 15 plat for a SBS or Chittin Shell Shield?  Come on!!  That's three wisps' GLSs(low blue by now if not green) at 5pp per!  Plus the loot in this zone even up TO the prince could provide enough money to buy a SBS or similar shield...much more AC, lighter, and a LOT more common!<br>-  + WIS or + INT???  Okay, peeps...lets not forget that it is only at level 20 when WIS and INT are even that important to PURE casters...raw mana is what is important to a caster/hybrid-caster at this point...not WIS or INT!<br>-  Druids not using it?  Hmm...  Well, if you were a druid and really hell bent on using this shield for the +1 WIS (again, remembering that it does you hardly any good before lvl 20)then I've got a crapload of soft wicker to unload on you for, say....10pp/1 AC?!?<br><br>The fact is that this shield is a total piece of crap no matter how you look at it.  It is an attempt on Verant's part to make it not TOO good.  Well...they sure succeeded there.<br><br>PS:  Shields are almost completely obsolete IMHO anyway.  Who needs a shield over level 17 anyway?  A paladin/SK would be better served with 2hs since the 2h weapon changes and since they can't dual wield...it makes only using a 1hs kind of silly to me.  And every other melee class can dual wield by then anyway...so why would THEY use a shield?  There ARE exceptions (CGS for big +wis bonus...Shield of the Slain Unicorn that started out as a good idea, but ended up sucking...and I'm sure a couple others) but as a whole, how often do you see someone over 20 with a shield?<br>&nbsp;<br>Humble druid extraordinaire!!&nbsp;&nbsp;=)<br><br>30th season  E'ci server</td></tr>
